%%%%%%%% Corrected announcement:

Dear Colleagues,

I would like to draw your attention to the programmes of the FSMP (Paris=20
Foundation of Mathematical Science), please have a look at the web page=20
of the Foundation:

http://www.sciencesmaths-paris.fr/

Notice that "Mathematical Sciences" include "Fundamental Computer=20
Science" and that PPS (http://www.pps.jussieu.fr/), as well as LIAFA=20
(http://www.liafa.jussieu.fr/) and the CS Department of the ENS=20
(http://www.di.ens.fr/) are part of the Foundation.

I'd like to insist in particular on:
- The post-doc programme, application deadline December 13th: if you=20
have good candidates please tell them to get in touch with me (or with=20
other colleagues of PPS) as soon as possible, deadline for application=20
December 13th.
- The Graduate School programme which provides funding for foreign=20
students in the masters of the FSMP, including Computer Science,=20
deadline for application December 14th. The two following Masters, in=20
which PPS is particularly involved, are associated to this programme:
MPRI, https://wikimpri.dptinfo.ens-cachan.fr/doku.php
LMFI, http://www.logique.jussieu.fr/www.M2-LMFI/

Don't hesitate to ask us for more information on these programmes and on=20
the application process.

Best regards,
Thomas Ehrhard
thomas.ehrhard@pps.jussieu.fr
